r in monetary support and also in-kind support though staff time, outreach and marketing, bike valet services, and waived fees for use of the Civic Auditorium parking lot. Platia Productions serves as the main organizer, planner and implementer of the event. The total contribution from the City over the next five-years would not exceed $125,000.", "Background", "The AltCar Expo, conference, and ride and drive was first held in Santa Monica in 2005 in collaboration with the Office of Sustainability and the Environment with the goal to provide an accessible and comprehensive setting where both the industry and general public could discover existing alternatives to traditional forms of transportation that rely on unleaded gasoline and diesel.", "Over the years, AltCar has gained national recognition and hosted the national debut of the Chevy Volt, the National Reveal of the Ford 150 CNG, the Global Debut of the Honda Plug-In, the kick-off of the Nissan LEAF and Toyota RAV EV Tours as well as many other fleet and public vehicle and infrastructure debuts. Speaker sessions have featured the top decision makers in Federal and State agencies as well as the directors of alternative technologies for all of the OEMs. AltCar also provides a platform for smaller alternative manufacturers and cutting-edge emerging products and technologies. AltCar also includes exhibitors and education on urban planning, mass transit, energy generation and use, policy and regulations, sustainable lifestyle choices, electric vehicle infrastructure, alternative fuel technology implementation and more. The 2016 AltCar Expo offered the most extensive array of battery electric, fuel-cell electric, plug-in hybrid, hybrid electric, natural gas, and propane vehicles available for consumers to view or test drive", "Discussion", "The City of Santa Monica has co-produced the AltCar Expo with Platia Productions for the last 11 years. Platia Productions was selected through the sole source process because Platia is the sole creator and owner of the AltCar Expo. This recommended award is made as an exception to the competitive bidding process pursuant to Section 2.24.080(d). The Memorandum of Understanding between the City of Santa Monica and Platia Productions would define the roles, responsibilities, and contributions of each party. Platia Productions has been approached by other southern California cities to relocate the event, but due to the ongoing support and shared sustainability goals both the City and Platia Productions are committed to the AltCar Expo remaining in the City of Santa Monica. The AltCar Expo is also produced by Platia Productions in Sacramento and Oakland.", "In past years the City has provided up to $25,000 in annual financial commitments to co-produce the AltCar Expo. The remaining cost to produce the event comes from the event sponsorships and tabling fees collected by Platia Productions. The City provides $15,000 in direct financial support to Platia Productions through the Office of Sustainability and the Environment. The City also supports the event through a $10,000 Air Quality Management District (AQMD) educational outreach grant awarded to the Street and Fleet Services Division and passed on to Platia. In addition, the City provides in-kind support though staff time, outreach and marketing, bike valet services, and waived fees in the amount of $39,000 per year for use of the Civic Auditorium parking lot. To date Platia Productions has received approximately $204,000 from the City for the AltCar Expo.", "Financial Impacts and Budget Actions", "The contract to be awarded to Platia Productions is for an amount not to exceed $125,000. Funds of $25,000 are available in the FY 2017-18 budget in the Public Works Department and the FY 2017-18 Capital Improvement Program budget. The contract will be charged to the following accounts:", "Account Number", "Amount", "014261.555060", "$15,000", "C440401.589000", "$10,000", "Total", "$25,000", "Future 