BB.", "Discussion", "Big Blue Bus and the City\u2019s Fire Department run continuous operations that stress the heavy-duty components and sensitive equipment on their heavy use vehicles. When these systems fail, the vehicles may be unable to continue operation, requiring the use of towing services. These vehicles may be towed to the BBB yard for maintenance and repair or directly to a vendor if serious repairs are needed. When components such as engines, transmissions, differentials and fuel systems fail, the vehicle\u2019s propulsion system is unable to provide power to operate the vehicle, safely; thereby, requiring a tow service to safely and carefully transport the vehicle. In the current fiscal year, 128 buses and 3 Fire Department vehicles were towed, either back to the bus yard, or to a vendor\u2019s offsite facility for repairs.", "Responsive and reliable towing services are necessary to ensure that BBB and Fire operations can continue unhindered. In addition to towing services, the vendor is required to carry absorbent and oil cleaning supplies, and may be required to clean spills as needed. To maintain clean and safe public spaces the vendor is required to have knowledge of proper spill containment and pick up procedures.", "Staff recommends that bid #4270 be awarded to Tom John\u2019s Towing for towing services related to BBB fleet and Fire heavy apparatus, based on the bid price submitted by this vendor and their previous work history with the City.", "Vendor/Consultant Selection", "On April 4, 2017, the City published Notices Inviting Bids to provide towing services for transit buses and fire apparatus in accordance with City specifications. The bid was posted on the City's online bidding site, and notices were advertised in the Santa Monica Daily Press in accordance with City Charter and Municipal Code provisions. One-thousand and one vendors were notified, of which eight vendors downloaded the bid. Two bids were received and publicly opened on April 2