nce with state and federal emission rules and regulations. The Cummins engines have several hundred parts, which make up the engine. Obtaining OEM engine parts will enable Big Blue Bus and Fire to service and maintain the engines to manufacture specifications and ensure proper efficient and effective operation.", "Vendor/Consultant Selection", "On February 27 2017, the City published Notices Inviting Bids to furnish and deliver genuine Cummins engine replacement parts in accordance with City specifications. The Notice was posted on the City's online bidding site, and notices were advertised in the Santa Monica Daily Press in accordance with City Charter and Municipal Code provisions. The City notified 746 vendors, of which 17 vendors downloaded the bid. Five bids were received and publicly opened on March 13, 2017 per the table below:", "Cost Estimate", "CAMENITA TRUCK CENTER", "COMPREHENSIVE HEALTH CARE SERVICES, LLC", "CUMMINS PACIFIC, LLC", "HARBOR DIESEL AND EQUIPMENT, INC.", "WESTERN TRUCK EXCHANGE", "Estimate - Based average part purchases", "$984,909", "$1,414,062", "$764,302", "$838,572", "$821,427", "Contract 5yr. Total", "$4,924,547", "$7,507,445", "$4,017,422", "$4,633,637", "$4,107,137", "Bids were evaluated based on the criteria in SMMC 2.24.072, including price, previous experience, ability to deliver, quality of product, and compliance with City specifications. Based on comparison of cost per part and positive history with the vendor, Cummins Pacific, LLC is recommended as the lowest and best bidder to provide Cummins OEM replacement parts in accordance with City specifications.", "Staff recommends that the Purchasing Services Manager issue a purchase order with Cummins Pacific, LLC, in the amount of $764,302 for one year, including a 10% contingency, four additional one-year renewal options to extend on the same terms and conditions, and a 2.5% increase per renewal year for a total not to exceed $4,017,422, with future year funding contingent on Coun