nd an AMREP body and for a vehicle with a Crane Carrier chassis with a Dadee body. The overall length of the vehicle with the Autocar chassis and Dadee body is 22\u201d shorter than the vehicle with the Autocar chassis and AMREP body and 6\u201d shorter than the vehicle with the Crane Carrier chassis and a Dadee body. The shorter body length is essential for RRR operations as these vehicles are driven in tight alleys and must maneuver the many constraints of the Santa Monica operating area.", "The Dadee Scorpion body has no cylinders inside the body. This eliminates the need for Fleet Management to conduct routine maintenance work inside the body. There is also no clean out area which eliminates the potential for a confined space hazard. RRR has been pleased with the performance of the vehicles in its fleet with Dadee Scorpion bodies and is moving to make its vehicle Fleet more uniform by utilizing one style of body for Side Loaders, further reducing maintenance costs and parts inventory.", "Bids were evaluated based on the criteria in SMMC 2.24.072, including price, ability to deliver, quality of product, and compliance with City specifications. Of the nine bids received, Los Angeles Freightliner bid eight different chassis and body configurations as separate bid submittals and RWC Group bid one, for a total of nine bids as shown in the table below. Los Angeles Freightliner submitted the only bid for the Autocar chassis and Dadee body configuration.", "Bidder", "Configuration", "Bid Price with Options", "Bid Price with Options and Discounts", "Los Angeles Freightliner", "Autocar / Dadee", "$1,736,444", "N/A", "Los Angeles Freightliner", "Autocar / AMREP", "$1,619,754", "N/A", "Los Angeles Freightliner", "Crane Carrier / AMREP", "$1,654,525", "N/A", "Los Angeles Freightliner", "Autocar / Wayne Curbtender", "$1,678,946", "N/A", "Los Angeles Freightliner", "Autocar / Wayne Hammerpak", "$1,678,946", "N/A", "Los Angeles Freightliner", "Crane Carrier / Wayne Curbtender",